                <fr:title text="matrix product is relational composition"><fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link href="/jms-00IN/" title="Relational composite" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN/" display-uri="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composition</fr:link></fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Under the correspondence between boolean <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> and finite <fr:link href="/jms-00I7/" title="Relation" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00I7/" display-uri="jms-00I7" type="local">relations</fr:link> (<fr:link href="/jms-00J1/" title="Correspondence between matrices and finite relations" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J1/" display-uri="jms-00J1" type="local">§ <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00J1/" display-uri="jms-00J1" /></fr:link>, <fr:link href="/jms-00IX/" title="Finite relations as matrices over the booleans" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IX/" display-uri="jms-00IX" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IX/" display-uri="jms-00IX" /></fr:link>), <fr:link href="/jms-00IV/" title="Product of matrices" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IV/" display-uri="jms-00IV" type="local">matrix products</fr:link> of boolean <fr:link href="/jms-00IS/" title="Matrix over a semiring" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IS/" display-uri="jms-00IS" type="local">matrices</fr:link> correspond to <fr:link href="/jms-00IN/" title="Relational composite" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00IN/" display-uri="jms-00IN" type="local">relational composites</fr:link>. In particular, given <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (l,m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[N\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we have:</html:p><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
 \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}} = \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} N\circ  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M
]]></fr:tex>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>We use the fact that the additive operation of the boolean semiring is disjunction and the multiplicative operation is conjunction:</html:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   {\mathopen {}\left (N\otimes  M\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} &= \bigoplus _{k\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}} N_{k,j}\odot  M_{i,k}
   \\
   &=
   \bigvee _{k\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}} N_{k,j}\land  M_{i,k}
   \\
   &=
   \exists  k\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathpunct {.}
   M_{i,k}\land  N_{k,j}
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
